*chuckle* ...who, for the record, wasn't me...  Never been married in game as either sex.  It's a touchy subject that brings up complicated issues.  Either it's strictly roleplay in which case it's hollow and meaningless, which I don't like the feeling of, or it's NOT strictly roleplay and ohhhh my god that's way more trouble.  A few years ago when I first started playing it was just creepy, to me... now it's dangerous.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also i don't think it's funny to be a fe-male to just get &quot;Phat-Uber Lewt&quot; <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't think it's funny, either.  I think it's bizarre yet touching that people react like that to an image, though I'm right there in that category.  When my real life eyes see a female avatar, I get real life reactions to it.  Doesn't matter who's hitting the keys, the rendered female image has an effect on me.  It doesn't make me DO anything,  but I do notice my response to it.<br>
<br>
As for my choice, it was pure pragmatism... if certain folks get more gifts, then that's the kind I want to be.  No humor about it.  Whatever line gets the most hugs and attention, that's the line I'll go stand in.<br>
