When someone gives your grief in GAME do YOU get mad or dose your CHARACTER get mad? hmmmmm i think you mis-understand alot of things here.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
When someone gives me IC grief my character would get angry.<br>
<br>
When somebody trains me or otherwise breaks the rules of the game then yes, I might get annoyed out of game.  Not because of what their character did but because of what their player did.  Of course, I try to never get angry about EQ stuff.  I don't always succeed but I have never, as a player, gotten angry about something someone's character did to my character.  Another LARP example, when a player set up a plot to kill my wife and child I took them out to dinner to congratulate them on great plot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>When you play your chara, you show a link NO MATTER WHAT to your chara, personality traits, ect.. ect.. Sometimes even you get personal traits from your character... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It is very hard to make a character that does not reflect on you in some way.  But that reflection can be the opposite of yourself, an idea you've always found interesting, or a reflection of another character from another source you enjoyed.  I've based a few characters on TV characters etc. and then let the character develop on its own once it hit play.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Its like creating a character in a good book. Or even better yet, this is a prime example of how the ancient greeks whorshiped their gods. They seen traits of the gods in them selfs. The gods were basicly Humans that where imortal....<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You've lost me.  I've created many characters for fiction.  I don't get angry or sad when bad things happen to them.  I take pleasure in knowing a great story is unfolding.  If nothing bad happened to them I'd be very dissapointed because it would be a terrible story.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
