<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ummm...no.  I'm saying whatever happens to my character happens to my character.  Whatever happens to me happens to me.  They are not the same thing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Hypocrite.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's a major fucking insult (I assume is aimed at me, and perhaps others) that you had better be able to back up.  And it's aimed at me, not my character.  If you wanted to call my current character a hypocrite you might have some call, though much of his hypocricy springs from multiple personality disorder.   And I wouldn't be insulted by you calling my character a hypocrite.<br>
<br>
At the core of this issue you seem to be thinking that a role-played romance somehow represents a real romance.  That's a VERY dangerous attitude to hold and I think you have already seen that the majority of players here disagree with you.  I've role-played plenty of romances with people I have no romantic interest in.  I've played romantic roles opposite people I would never date in a million years.  If you can't tell the difference...I again question if playing is the best plan for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dessirra>dessirra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 269<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/24/03 1:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3921.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In the eyes of the FV Community...Id like to know</span><hr size=1> My char Poyson doesn't accept gifts and I know several other female characters that don't.  <br>
