I find the statement curious... what is it about &quot;accepting a gift&quot; that is a real life male trait?  Maybe I'm just misreading it, which isn't unlikely...  Is it that males are unconcerned with a hidden agenda behind a gift being given?  I confess that I'm clueless.<br>
<br>
I have given many gifts to many players in the form of time, money, assistance, and items.  I have no idea what percentage of them were male and female, since both I and my character respond to a perceived need rather than an avatar image.<br>
<br>
But of those, I can recall only a single one who summarily refused a gift, saying in effect that they wanted to make their own way in the world without help.  That one was a male avatar.<br>
<br>
In real life, interestingly enough, I MUCH prefer to avoid receiving gifts and attention for good things that I might do.  It makes me uncomfortable.  I am happiest when good deeds are pleasantly but quietly received, and when people show their appreciation for me in ways other than the presentation of things.  So for me, at least, having a character set up to receive things... is a pretty far cry from the person I really am.<br>
