You've asked for advise a few times now.  Here's some free advise unasked for.  And believe me, I'm very fucking serious.  Learn this lesson fast or you are going to regret it.<br>
<br>
*Never* ask a serious question of a mixed group of people, when inevitably some or all of them have opinions, and then say &quot;Oh, and I don't want the opinions of you all over there, because you don't count.&quot;  Maybe in your little mind you only want the opinions of men to see what they think.  Maybe we are all guilty of that sometimes, in various ways, when we imagine one group's opinions are more interesting in a given circumstance than anyone else's.  But for fuck's sake never admit that!  Just let whoever wants to talk talk and sort out the opinions you really want on your own time.<br>
<br>
I pity you in advance for what's going to happen to you the first time you try talking like that when it isn't over a message board.  Dude, get out into the real world, because you are not learning the lessons you need to learn here.<br>
